## 🎨 Design (5)

### 6. Logo
**Role:** You are a senior logo designer.
**Objective:** Design a logo for [brand name/type of business].
**Background:** [Brief brand context — new brand, rebrand, industry, etc.]
**Target Audience:** [Describe brand's customer base].
**Requirements:** Modern, distinctive design; specify color palette, style (minimalist/abstract/wordmark), and any symbolic elements to include.
**Constraints:** Must be original (no resemblance to existing logos); avoid [specific exclusions, e.g., animal imagery, certain colors].
**Output Format:** A detailed image-generation prompt describing the logo mark, typography, colors, and layout.
**Evaluation Criteria:** Originality, scalability across sizes/platforms, and alignment with brand identity.

---

### 7. Poster
**Role:** You are a senior graphic designer specializing in print and digital posters.
**Objective:** Design a poster to promote [event/product/cause].
**Background:** [Context — event details, purpose, launch, etc.]
**Target Audience:** [Who will see this poster].
**Requirements:** Eye-catching visual hierarchy, bold headline text, key details (date/place/offer) clearly visible, consistent brand colors.
**Constraints:** Must remain legible at both large print size and small digital thumbnail; no copyrighted imagery.
**Output Format:** A detailed image-generation prompt covering layout, text placement, color scheme, and visual style.
**Evaluation Criteria:** Clarity of message at a glance, visual appeal, and legibility across sizes.

---

### 8. Banner
**Role:** You are a senior digital designer specializing in web and social banners.
**Objective:** Design a banner for [website/campaign/promotion].
**Background:** [Context — where the banner will be used, campaign purpose].
**Target Audience:** [Website visitors / campaign audience].
**Requirements:** Clear call-to-action, concise headline, brand-consistent colors and fonts, balanced composition.
**Constraints:** Must fit standard banner dimensions ([specify size, e.g., 1200x300px]); avoid cluttered text.
**Output Format:** A detailed image-generation prompt specifying layout, text, colors, and dimensions.
**Evaluation Criteria:** Message clarity within 3 seconds of viewing, and adherence to size/platform constraints.

---

### 9. Social Media Post
**Role:** You are a senior social media graphic designer.
**Objective:** Design a social media post visual for [platform] promoting [topic/product/announcement].
**Background:** [Context — campaign, brand voice, occasion].
**Target Audience:** [Platform's typical audience, e.g., Instagram users aged 18-35].
**Requirements:** Scroll-stopping visual, on-brand colors/fonts, short punchy text overlay, platform-appropriate dimensions.
**Constraints:** Must follow platform-specific size guidelines (e.g., 1080x1080 for Instagram square); no copyrighted material.
**Output Format:** A detailed image-generation prompt including composition, text, and color palette.
**Evaluation Criteria:** Visual appeal, brand consistency, and effectiveness in stopping the scroll.

---

### 10. Brochure
**Role:** You are a senior print/digital brochure designer.
**Objective:** Design a brochure for [business/product/service].
**Background:** [Context — purpose of brochure, distribution method].
**Target Audience:** [Who will receive/read this brochure].
**Requirements:** Clear sectioning (cover, inside info, contact/CTA), consistent branding, professional layout with visual and text balance.
**Constraints:** Must fit standard brochure fold format (e.g., tri-fold A4); avoid overcrowding with text.
**Output Format:** A detailed design specification/prompt covering each panel's content and layout.
**Evaluation Criteria:** Information clarity, visual professionalism, and ease of navigation through panels.

