## 📢 Marketing (5)

### 11. LinkedIn Post
**Role:** You are a senior content marketer specializing in professional/B2B communication.
**Objective:** Write a LinkedIn post about [topic/announcement/insight].
**Background:** [Context — company update, thought leadership, product launch, etc.]
**Target Audience:** [Professional audience — e.g., industry peers, potential clients, recruiters].
**Requirements:** Engaging hook in the first line, clear value/insight, professional yet conversational tone, relevant hashtags.
**Constraints:** Keep under [200-300] words; avoid overly salesy language.
**Output Format:** A ready-to-post LinkedIn text with suggested hashtags.
**Evaluation Criteria:** Engagement potential (likes/comments), professionalism, and clarity of message.

---

### 12. Email Campaign
**Role:** You are a senior email marketing strategist.
**Objective:** Write an email campaign for [product launch/promotion/newsletter].
**Background:** [Context — campaign goal, audience segment, occasion].
**Target Audience:** [Subscriber segment — e.g., existing customers, new leads].
**Requirements:** Compelling subject line, clear body structure (hook, value, CTA), personalization placeholders, mobile-friendly formatting.
**Constraints:** Keep body concise (under 150 words); one clear CTA only.
**Output Format:** Subject line + email body, ready to insert into an email marketing tool.
**Evaluation Criteria:** Open-rate potential (subject line strength), clarity of CTA, and relevance to audience.

---

### 13. Instagram Caption
**Role:** You are a senior social media copywriter.
**Objective:** Write an Instagram caption for [post topic/product/campaign].
**Background:** [Context — brand voice, occasion, campaign].
**Target Audience:** [Instagram audience demographic].
**Requirements:** Catchy opening line, concise and relatable tone, relevant emojis (if appropriate), call-to-action, hashtag suggestions.
**Constraints:** Keep under [125] words; avoid overly promotional language.
**Output Format:** Ready-to-post caption text with hashtag list.
**Evaluation Criteria:** Engagement potential and alignment with brand voice.

---

### 14. Ad Copy
**Role:** You are a senior performance marketing copywriter.
**Objective:** Write ad copy for [platform, e.g., Google Ads/Facebook Ads] promoting [product/service].
**Background:** [Context — campaign goal, offer details].
**Target Audience:** [Specific customer segment being targeted].
**Requirements:** Strong headline, clear value proposition, urgency/CTA, benefit-focused language.
**Constraints:** Must fit platform character limits (e.g., Google Ads: 30-character headlines, 90-character descriptions).
**Output Format:** Headline + description variations (2-3 options), ready for ad platform input.
**Evaluation Criteria:** Clarity of offer, persuasiveness, and adherence to character limits.

---

### 15. Product Description
**Role:** You are a senior e-commerce copywriter.
**Objective:** Write a product description for [product name/type].
**Background:** [Context — product features, brand positioning].
**Target Audience:** [Target customer profile for this product].
**Requirements:** Highlight key features and benefits, sensory/descriptive language, include specifications where relevant, persuasive closing line.
**Constraints:** Keep within [100-150] words; avoid exaggerated or misleading claims.
**Output Format:** A ready-to-publish product description for an e-commerce listing.
**Evaluation Criteria:** Clarity, persuasiveness, and accuracy of product representation.

